<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="key">
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,863,1073]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">A8 (A7) Wax glands of overwintering larvae with double-walled facets secreting glossy, stiff, straight or curved tubes of wax; galls usually with protruding needles and hairs or waxy bloom ................................................................................................................................A9</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,863,1073]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
